main event: On June 24, 1963 at 2100 hours, ECHO crossed the equator heading NE and was confirmed to be the 16263 satellite ECHO I.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 7 minutes., The satellite was identified to be at about 17 degrees S latitude, 1400 miles south of the reported time., The document is a page from a Project Blue Book UFO report., The event involved confirmation of a satellite's position and trajectory., There are no photographs included in the report.
